$interpreted: Naya: Angel, this is the safest route to the Slums. It's the best we can manage for now.
Angelia: Don't worry...let's keep going.
Cowardly Bandit: Hey, it's pretty late to run into more travelers.
Naya: State your identity!
Cowardly Bandit: Sh-Sh-Shut up and give us all your money, now!
Angelia: Please, calm down. We don't have anything worth of value left...
Cowardly Bandit: LIAR! Dressed in such glamour, and you tell me that you're penniless?!
Angelia: I...
Cowardly Bandit: You nobles! Always stepping over poor folk like us, we've had enough!
Cowardly Bandit: Return what once was rightfully ours!
Angelia: I'm sorry! I didn't mean to, are you hurt?
Cowardly Bandit: Waaaoooh~ Don't come near! It was our fault, oh noble!
Cowardly Bandit: Please have mercy! Life in the Slums, it's barely liveable... We only went along with the plan to have a chance at something better...
Angelia: You live in the Slums?
Cowardly Bandit: Yes, yes we do, we......
Naya: Angel, WATCH OUT!
Naya: Whew~ Didn't expect to see beasts near the Slums, that was way too close...
Angelia: Why...is this happening...?
Angelia: These folk are living in such dangerous conditions...but the Kingdom has done nothing about it...
Naya: Angel. We have to keep moving.
Angelia: Hmm...
Naya: Whew...Angel, we made it!
Angelia: I've never... seen the castle like this before.
Angelia: If only the nobles could shine some light upon the poor folk,
Angelia: they wouldn't have to live in the darkness, right?
Naya: Angel, don't blame yourself.
Angelia: But if I could do a little something, at least they'd be saved from the hunger and cold...
Naya: Let's worry about this another time. Angel, time to go inside.
Angelia: ...Alright.
Hyacinthus: Nigel, these deals are risky. You can't keep doing this.
Nigel: Eh, I know.
Hyacinthus: I can tell by your voice you're not going to stop!
Nigel: And your point is?
Nigel: Who's that? Newcomers?
Hyacinthus: Never seen those faces before. Taking refuge in the Slums isn't something you do when you have a choice...
